I have a list of strings, and I want to sort them in case-sensative way. For example, I have a list of strings: ["a", "A", "b", "B", "c", "C"] and I want to sort them in case-sensative way, so the result will be: ["A", "a", "B", "b", "C", "c"].
I tried to use sort() function, but it sorts them in case-insensitive way.
How can I sort them in case-sensative way?
You can use localeCompare() to compare strings in a case-sensitive way:
["a", "A", "b", "B", "c", "C"].sort((a, b) => a.localeCompare(b))
// ["A", "a", "B", "b", "C", "c"]
You can also use a custom compare function:
["a", "A", "b", "B", "c", "C"].sort((a, b) => a.toLowerCase().localeCompare(b.toLowerCase()))
// ["A", "a", "B", "b", "C", "c"]

Machine learning is a branch of artificial intelligence that deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from data and make predictions or decisions without being explicitly programmed. Machine learning algorithms are used in a wide range of applications, including image recognition, natural language processing, and recommendation systems.
In this article, we will explain all machine learning algorithms with examples and code in Python. We will start with the basics of machine learning and then move on to more advanced algorithms. By the end of this article, you will have a good understanding of how machine learning algorithms work and how to use them in your own projects.
The first step in any machine learning project is to collect data. This data can come from a variety of sources, such as sensors, surveys, or historical records. Once you have collected your data, you need to clean it and prepare it for analysis. This involves removing any duplicates or errors, and ensuring that the data is in a format that can be easily analyzed.
Once your data is clean and ready, you can start to explore it. This involves looking for patterns and trends in the data, and trying to understand what the data is telling you. This is an important step, as it will help you to decide which machine learning algorithm to use.
There are many different machine learning algorithms, each with its own strengths and weaknesses. Some of the most popular algorithms include:
Linear regression is a simple algorithm that is used to predict a continuous outcome variable. It works by fitting a line to the data, and then using that line to make predictions.
Logistic regression is a more advanced algorithm that is used to predict a binary outcome variable. It works by fitting a curve to the data, and then using that curve to make predictions.
Decision trees are a type of algorithm that is used to make decisions based on the data. They work by splitting the data into smaller and smaller groups, until a decision can be made.
Random forests are a type of algorithm that is used to make predictions based on a group of decision trees. They work by averaging the predictions of the individual decision trees.
Support vector machines are a type of algorithm that is used to make predictions based on a group of support vectors. They work by finding the best support vectors to use for prediction.
Once you have chosen an algorithm, you need to train it on your data. This involves feeding the algorithm the data and letting it learn from it. The algorithm will then be able to make predictions on new data.
Once your algorithm is trained, you can start to use it to make predictions on new data. This is where the power of machine learning really comes into play. By using an algorithm to make predictions, you can save time and money, and improve the accuracy of your predictions.
Machine learning is a powerful tool that can be used to solve a wide range of problems. By understanding how machine learning algorithms work, you can use them to improve your own projects and make better decisions.
